<br>
1) I explained to group that cleric and chanter would split the gems, exceptions would be to give gems out to those needing them for quests.<br>
<br>
2) I kept any junk loot not claimed by the other members to sell as merchant fodder.<br>
<br>
3) I split platinum coins only as each member decided to leave group. Destroyed silver and copper.<br>
<br>
4) Even though I carried peridots on me I only buffed myself, the MA, and the enchanter with this and used Jasper on the others.<br>
<br>
5) I never rolled on items unless I had a twink that could use the item. At the time Packfulla was my twink, but I was playing a Ranger(main) and SK(twink).<br>
<br>
Now I do not consider my methods in KC as greed. I consider them as profit maximization. I leveled Packfulla from 40-52 in KC and during that time I made a total of 2500pp profit. That rate is not shit compared to buying a stack of peridots which on average cost 230pp.<br>
<br>
Don't never bash a cleric or enchanter and call them greedy until you personally play one and see that they are very expensive classes to play. In addition to buying gems there is the buying of spells which becomes rather expensive with the 50+ dropped spells. <br>
<br>
