I currently play a 48sk, now i usually solo, infact have pretty much soloed, or on a rare occasion partnered with a shammy since i was about lvl 42, and before that 31-38.  In a group im often times either the puller, if no monky around, or the MT, because i jsut do quite a bit of dmg. Ive never had an instance of a cleric charging me for heals or buffs. Tanks and healers balance each other out. A cleric is pretty useless without a tank, however i am considered a tank, and i can usually fare jsut fine without a cleric. This is not to say that they dont help, i do like a nice heal once in a while. But the important thing is to show common courtesy. I dont charge ppl for my services as a tank, because my wpn cost like 20k, im not gonna charge 5pp per every hit i make, or pull a mob go FD, and then ask the cleric for a donation before i engage the mob. That would be a jackass thing to do. I mean money for tanks is a lot harder to come by then it is for porters or rezzers etc. What kind of services can i perform? Not many, nothing that will really turn a profit. <br>
<br>
