ass=title> Re: STOOPID CLERICS</span><hr size=1> Ive played a warrior, casters and now my cleric.  I can understand the point of view youre coming from about not having any way to make money since you dont have a &quot;money maker&quot; like rezz, or clarity, or other buffs.<br>
<br>
I have never been a greedy cleric, I chose to play this class i knew what I was coming into as far as cost.  Sure some classes have it &quot;easier&quot; to make money with their abilties then others, you live with what u chose, good or bad.  <br>
<br>
I've always believed everything is a group effort.  Clerics die without a good tank, tanks die without a good cleric. This is true. But after hitting 50 and really starting to become a cleric  you really begin to understand why most people believe that  clerics ML gems and such to help in costs with dots etc.<br>
<br>
Example: Our 60 tank wants to hit  a high lvl zone (along with others) in hopes of good drops.  We have a group: 3 tanks, me, and other support classes.  Sure you need the tanks to succeed, you also need the cleric, no arguement.   I buy KEI 3-4 times over the night 100pp a pop to keep em coming (even after deaths), keep myself and 3 tanks symboled (if there was an enchanter Id symbol them too) , this is refreshed 3 or 4 times over 4 people in a few hours.  <br>
<br>
So thats what, around 500pp for a couple hours out of my pocket.  now imagine this over a long period of time, say hate, or any plane.  Or just a long day of exp grinding.  <br>
<br>
Is it &quot;fair&quot; that clerics should ML and get all the whatever loot to sell for &quot;profit&quot;?  Well thats dertimined by YOU, personal feeling whatever. Its just a common curteousy that has become a habit of most people to offset  expenses for the cleric.  <br>
<br>
Without  the cleric you may have a regen bp or a clickable heal off your 90k armor AFTER the fight, but nothing can replace a good healer DURING one. Who also needs good armor, good spells, and expensive gems to keep everyone alive.  Believe or not theres a balance.  Even with this generosity.<br>
<br>
Sure if you dont wanna share with your local cleric,  then they cant buy what they need to keep you alive.  <br>
<br>
Our tank says, &quot;A warrior is only as good as his cleric&quot;  Even though I believe the saying goes both ways, I also know all the armor on norrath/luclin can't keep you alive, but your cleric can.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  If this werent true i wouldnt see the most shouts for &quot;Any clerics LFG?&quot;<br>
<br>
Clerics lose money everyday protecting the world.  Doesnt hurt to help them out  I sometimes make more then enough to cover costs, but more often  I lose money. We ALL lose money.  YES u need armor and weapons. to protect the cleric.  BUT Clerics need more then that to keep you alive. And they need a lot more, more often. <br>
<br>
But even through all of that, not all of us are greedy, cause we understand that it's hard for everyone to make ends meet sometimes, even in EQ. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
