Usually, the cleric is the ML in a single group, and will randomly split platinum and gold (as a member leaves or disbands), or one big split at the end of the group. Any merchant fodder is usually agreed to go to the cleric, to cover his reagent costs. Sometimes, the group would stick together as the cleric sold items and split the money received from the sale.  I even once was in a group in OS, where after the 3 hour killing spree, the cleric had all group mates &lt;/ran 100&gt; for items and gems. The extra/odd gem(s) was agreed upon as being rewarded to the cleric, to cover his expenses in reagent costs.  No argument/question.<br>
I have been on many Planes raids, where the raid leader/looter kept ALL gems/crowns/etc.  Also, I have been to Planes where the looter would distribute gems to all players present, either during short breaks or after raid. Never have I been to a Planes raid where money was awarded to groups, as the objective in those is mainly to obtain planar gear drops or exp.<br>
I must say that I have NEVER been in a group where the cleric (or chanter even) have charged for any buff, no matter what was entailed to cast it (reagent/mana/etc.).  However, when I play my SK, and I know that symbols are going to be important for the fight, and the zone/mobs don't offer much of an opportunity to reward us in cash/merchant fodder, I will offer the cleric money to purchase more reagents (or ask the group to chip in). Hell, had an LGuk group other night, where I gave the cleric 150PP in advance to purchase peridots that I knew he was going to use on my fat arse.<br>
I think someone said this before, but I'm just too lazy to go back thru the post.....If the cleric won't symbol w/out a donation, he better keep the group alive when they can't/won't cough up the cash.<br>
OK, I have used my allotted time here.<br>
